event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Database Forensics & User Activity Report\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThe **openagentic_admin MCP server** (`10.43.224.106:8080`) has suffered a complete outage. All 4 requested SQL queries, the Milvus collection probe, and every audit-log endpoint failed with `ECONNREFUSED`. **Zero of the 4 forensic queries could execute.** This represents a deterioration from the previous audit round (15 minutes ago), where the same server returned HTTP 500 with a Python logging bug — it has now progressed to a full TCP refusal.\n\n---\n\n### Probe Execution Results\n\n| # | Query | Tool | Status | Error |\n|:-:|-------|------|:------:|-------|\n| 1 | User activity by session count | `admin_system_postgres_raw_query` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 2 | ChatMessage role distribution | `admin_system_postgres_raw_query` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 3 | SystemConfiguration dump | `admin_system_postgres_raw_query` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 4 | Milvus collection info | `admin_system_milvus_get_collection_info` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 5 | Usage statistics (audit) | `admin_audit_get_usage_statistics` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 6 | User chat history (audit) | `admin_audit_get_user_chats` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 7 | Login history (audit) | `admin_audit_get_login_history` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 8 | Error analysis (audit) | `admin_audit_get_error_analysis` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 9 | User list | `admin_system_users_list_all` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 10 | Flowise chatflows | `flowise_list_chatflows` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 11 | Prometheus alerts | `prometheus_alerts` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n\n---\n\n### What IS Reachable\n\n| Service | Status | Notes |\n|---------|:------:|-------|\n| **LangGraph** | ✅ Healthy | `http://openagentic-langgraph:3100` |\n| **CrewAI** | ✅ Healthy | `http://openagentic-crewai:3200` |\n| **Flowise** | ❌ Unhealthy | Persistent since first audit |\n| **Loki** | ⚠️ Partial | Responds but returns 0 streams / 0 errors |\n\n---\n\n### Failure Progression Timeline\n\nThis session alone has captured the admin MCP degrading in real time:\n\n```\nT+0 min   ─ HTTP 500: \"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\"  (Python logging bug)\nT+15 min  ─ ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080                        (Process crashed / pod evicted)\n```\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"Admin MCP Failure Cascade\",\n  \"layout\": \"horizontal\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"healthy\", \"label\": \"Admin MCP\\nHealthy\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"success\"},\n    {\"id\": \"logging\", \"label\": \"LogRecord Bug\\nHTTP 500\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"warning\"},\n    {\"id\": \"crash\", \"label\": \"Process Crash\\nECONNREFUSED\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"impact\", \"label\": \"Total Data Layer\\nBlackout\", \"shape\": \"hexagon\", \"color\": \"error\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"healthy\", \"target\": \"logging\", \"label\": \"T+0\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"logging\", \"target\": \"crash\", \"label\": \"T+15m\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"crash\", \"target\": \"impact\", \"label\": \"Now\", \"style\": \"animated\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Answers to Your Questions (from Historical Audit Data)\n\nSince direct queries are blocked, here's what we know from **previous forensic audits** stored in memory:\n\n| Question | Answer | Source |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| **Most active users?** | ❌ Cannot determine — User×Session JOIN never executed across any audit | All 3 audits failed |\n| **Total messages?** | ❌ Cannot determine — ChatMessage role distribution never returned | All 3 audits failed |\n| **System configuration?** | ❌ Cannot determine — SystemConfiguration table never queried | All 3 audits failed |\n| **Milvus collections?** | ❌ Cannot determine — Milvus calls failed in every audit | All 3 audits failed |\n\n> [!CAUTION]\n> **Across 4 full audit attempts in this session, the admin MCP has never once returned data.** The `openagentic_admin` server has been non-functional for the entire observation window. No PostgreSQL, Redis, or Milvus data has ever been successfully retrieved.\n\n---\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\n| Factor | Evidence | Confidence |\n|--------|----------|:----------:|\n| **Python LogRecord bug** | `\"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\"` — a known Python logging library issue where structured logging conflicts with stdlib | High |\n| **Unhandled exception → crash** | Progressed from 500 errors to ECONNREFUSED within 15 minutes | High |\n| **No restart recovery** | Pod is not auto-recovering — suggests either CrashLoopBackOff or missing liveness probe | Medium |\n| **No alerting** | Prometheus was also behind the same proxy and is now unreachable; Loki shows 0 active streams | High |\n\n---\n\n### Recommended Actions\n\n| # | Action | Priority | Rationale |\n|:-:|--------|:--------:|-----------|\n| 1 | **`kubectl get pods -n openagentic` — check openagentic_admin pod status** | **P0** | Confirm CrashLoopBackOff or OOMKill |\n| 2 | **`kubectl logs -n openagentic <openagentic-admin-pod> --previous`** | **P0** | Capture crash stack trace before log rotation |\n| 3 | **Fix the LogRecord bug** — likely a `logging.Formatter` using `args` as a field name conflicting with Python's `LogRecord.args` | **P0** | Root cause of the cascade |\n| 4 | **Add liveness/readiness probes** to the openagentic_admin deployment | **P1** | Kubernetes should auto-restart on crash |\n| 5 | **Decouple Prometheus/Flowise routing** from the admin MCP proxy | **P1** | Single point of failure taking down all observability |\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> The admin MCP at `10.43.224.106:8080` is the **single gateway** for PostgreSQL, Redis, Milvus, Prometheus, Flowise, and all audit APIs. Its failure creates a **total observability blackout** — you cannot monitor the system that monitors the system. This is a critical architectural risk."}

